comments.body:
@andrew-kennedy I don't know. Are you sure you used `podman generate systemd --new` before? If you just use `podman generate systemd` does it work?
If the container always exits after the update process this will cause a systemd restart and if the container does not store the update status and start to update again this will end in a loop obviously. I think you may have to mount another directory to keep the update state?

I don't think podman is doing anything wrong here.
